Intro

Let's compare results of ANOVAs like I did previously that 1). had kill factor in the model fixed effects and 2). ran on all three dates each year. I.e.

for the previous version versus:

Note kill is still in the model but as a random effect since cover crop is not completely randomly assigned to plots but rather is a split plot within the kill main plots both before and after termination. I.e. you have to account for this possible covariance somehow, but you dont need to have it as a fixed effect taking away from your degrees of freedom for error terms like in the previous version.

Soil moisture (gravimetric water content)

Next, there was a cover X year X date interaction in the every date anova.

And we have a cover X year effect now focusing on prekill, so these might be pointing to the same thing, let's see:

##   X  cc year lsmean   SE   df lower.CL upper.CL .group
## 1 1  hv 2012   0.22 0.01 8.56     0.20     0.24     a 
## 2 2  cc 2012   0.21 0.01 8.56     0.19     0.23     a 
## 3 3 n00 2012   0.19 0.01 8.56     0.17     0.21      b
## 4 4 n00 2013   0.14 0.01 8.56     0.12     0.16     a 
## 5 5  hv 2013   0.12 0.01 8.56     0.10     0.14      b
## 6 6  cc 2013   0.12 0.01 8.56     0.10     0.14      b

The prekill means separations are the same no matter the inclusion of postkill and midseason data, i.e. in this case having a model that ignores kill as a fixed effect prekill and leaves out the last two dates doesn't change our takeaways for cover crop effect on soil moisture prekill.

Aggregate mean weight diameter

There was nothing prekill before removing the kill factor and the two latter dates. What about now, with an anova that just has the year, cover crop, and year by cover crop, and just the same first date both years?

##   X    term     sumsq    meansq NumDF    DenDF statistic   p.value sig fvsigfig
## 1 1      cc 1.7829176 0.8914588     2 48.98537  1.223660 0.3029843  NA      1.2
## 2 2    year 0.7587538 0.7587538     1 45.25513  1.041503 0.3128971  NA      1.0
## 3 3 cc:year 2.4590114 1.2295057     2 48.98537  1.687680 0.1955234  NA      1.7

No, there is still no effect of cover crop before termination on MWD.

Summary

  • For MBC, prekill there is a new and slightly different result that there is a year by depth by cover interaction, but it still points to vetch having more MBC than clover or non planted.

  • However, for HWC, MWD, soil moisture, PMN, and PMC, this new analysis doesn't change our takehomes.
